on for star-forming galaxies at $z=3.7$. These\nresults support scenarios where massive galaxies at $z=$ 3.5-4.0 quench by\nconsuming/expelling all the gas rather than by reducing the efficiency of the\nconversion of their gas into stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Jun 2022 18:37:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-07"}
