gence conditions.\n  We also establish an arithmetic counterpart of theorems of Lefschetz and Nori\nby providing a bound on the index, in the \\'etale fundamental group of an\narithmetic surface, of the closed subgroup generated by the \\'etale fundamental\ngroups of some arithmetic curve and of some compact Riemann surfaces mapping to\nthe arithmetic surface.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Jun 2022 18:39:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 14 Sep 2022 09:37:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-15"}
