superdiffusive large time scaling. We also consider\ntime-changed versions where the walk is subordinated to a continuous-time point\nprocess such as the time-fractional Poisson process. This defines a new class\nof biased continuous-time random walks exhibiting several regimes of anomalous\ndiffusion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Jun 2022 14:46:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 20 Nov 2022 15:27:49 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 6 Dec 2022 09:28:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-04"}
